    {
      "id": "d51127ea1c0fb7850414a6d2846bee94780fdcec",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-09 22:51:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIf ldiskfs patches need to be changed, you should very likely be copying those patches to a new rhel6.5 subdirectory and changing them there.  Then make a new series file for 6.5 that is selected from the autoconf stuff if the correct kernel version number is detected.\n\nFurther, it looks like HAVE_LDISKFS_GET_BLOCKS is used only by osd_io.c.  Is that correct?  If so, you should be setting HAVE_LDISKFS_GET_BLOCKS at configure time with an autoconf check, not hard coding it into ldiskfs with a patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
